captions.text:
Hey Vsauce I'm Jake and nobody likes pop-up
windows...unless you're using them to play

pong in this awesome game. Which of course
you'll win because of your violent power.com.

But let's stare at this incredibly long zooming
image and check out some more DONGs. Things
you Can Do Online Now, Guys.

Lost in the Desert could be the longest joke
ever written . It consists of over 10,800

words and is 137.8 feet long from top to bottom.
If we use How Many Tall, that makes it 3,514.9

skittles tall or 27.53 Danny DeVitos. As a
comparison I am, sadly, only 1.2 Danny DeVitos
tall.

Huh my life is in Shambles, a really fun first
person shooter created by Notch. You mow down

zombies and soldiers, picking up better weapons
and collecting yellow balls to increase your
score.

If you get lost on these zombie infested streets,
try maze escape. A game where you have to

navigate as quickly as you can while out running
a wall of lava. If you keep running into the

walls you might be...hmm...what are some other
words for being drunk.com? Maybe Ultra Slizzard,
solidly newcastled or even exhaustively potted.

After you've sobered up, shoot an arrow off
your friends head....but be careful not to

brutally murder them in the process ...ee
ya know maybe you should practice a little

bit more with Bow Master Japan. Aim at the
targets and hit them all before time runs
out

Continue to race the clock with clockbusters
at veer.com. You have 60 seconds to figure
out the movie title using only three images.

And keep track of those precious seconds with
animaclock. There are different faces to choose
from or you can code your own.

Then create beautiful and weird growths with
this recursion toy. Set the parameters and

watch it grow. There are multiple different
behaviors and styles to choose from, all of
which will create a really unique image.

Continue growing things with Watashi Wa. A
relaxing game where you create a forest in

the desert by throwing green seeds everywhere
to create trees. Or just be a plant in SPY,

a game that has you sneaking around levels
and avoiding being seen. It is a clever and

fun game that you have to take your time with
to win.

For a little more action, test your space
bar mashing ability with Press the Spacebar

2000. See how fast you can go for 5, 10, or
20 seconds. When you are done you'll get your

score from these random dudes. Sup dudes (sup
jake)

Let's keep the action going with Hello Run
which is really fun and harder than it looks.

Make your way through the corridors by going
over and under obstacles that are constantly
changing and making you lose.

Here are four words I never thought I'd say,
Miley Cyrus's Infinite Tongue. I mean...there
ya go world.

And ya know what's boring? YouTube. Ya know
what's not boring? Yooouuuuutuuube.com, a

new way to watch youtube videos .... that
might make you throw up....if the catleidoscope
hasn't already done that.

If you're not part of the 25% of the population
who sent in Cookie Clicker then here is Cookie
Clicker, where you click a cookie FOREVER.

After all those sweets, eat some carrots in
Babbit, an adorable game where you guide a

rabbit through different rows trying to collect
carrots and avoid bombs lest you want to become
a rabbit pie.

But Hey Girl, I bet you were wishin' that
this website was entirely photos of Ryan Gosling.
Wish granted.

Now let me draw you a picture with light using
Zen Photo garden. Adjust the diffusion, reflective

and transmissive properties to create your
work of art.

Then play One and one Story. It is a really
beautiful puzzle platformer that has you journeying

to find and be reconnected with your love.
The instructions act like a book to push the
narrative along.

If you can't find your one, remember that
some of us are looking at the sky. Choose

a location on the map highlighted in blue
and it automatically saves until the next
person comes along to change it.

While you're doing these DONGs, I made a music
playlist, a leanback, over on WEsauce of Just

Awesome Music. These jams are perfect to listen
to while you're exploring things you can do

online now, guys. So check out the Leanback
by clicking here or the link at the top of

the description if you're on mobile because
I respect and appreciate you...and, as always,
thanks for watching.

title: How Many Danny DeVitos Are You? -- DONG
